Preheat the oven to 190C/170C Fan/Gas 5.Put the olive oil and sage leaves in a pan. Fry until crisp and then immediately remove the sage leaves and set aside.Add the sliced onions to the same pan. Cook over a low to moderate heat for 20-30 minutes, stirring occasionally, until soft and caramelised. Set aside.Lay the puff pastry out on a lined baking tray and top with the caramelised onions, leaving a border all around. Top with the potatoes and grated gruy√®re. Bake for 20-25 minutes.Remove from the oven when golden-brown, garnish with the crisp sage leaves and serve.